OPERATIONAL CORRECTIVE - interleave instruction during long non-spool stretches (reinforced 2026-06-15, own mid-chain-stall in ccsniff-fix fire): scanStalledTurns flags deviation.mid-chain-stall when a non-terminal turn goes >300s with no spool dispatch, even while the agent is actively working through non-spool tool calls (Read of sibling-repo source, Edit of files, Bash running external node test/build). The watcher only sees the spool, so heads-down implement+test stretches read as a stall. Corrective: during any multi-minute non-spool stretch, interleave an instruction dispatch (cheap, idempotent) to keep the watcher seeing activity; and prefer routing investigation through spool verbs (codesearch/exec_js/fs/git) over raw Read/Bash where a verb exists. Witnessed benign-but-real: claude-l turn_idx 8 idle_ms 306501 in PLAN while editing+node-testing ccsniff.